==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Latin [[papyrus#Latin|papyrus]], from Greek [[πάπυρος]] ‘paper-reed’, of unknown origin.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/pəˈpaɪrəs/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪrəs|-aɪrəs]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|papyri|pl2=papyruses}}

#A [[plant]] in the [[sedge]] family, ''Cyperus papyrus'', native to the Nile river valley.
#A material similar to [[paper]] made from the papyrus plant.
#A [[scroll]] or [[document]] written on papyrus.

====Translations====
;plant
*German: [[Papyrus]] {{m}}, [[Echter Papyrus]] {{m}}, [[Papyrusstaude]] {{f}}

;material
*German: [[Papyrus]] {{m}}

;document
*German: [[Papyrus]] {{m}}

====Related Words====
*[[papyrology]]
*[[papyrologist]]

====Usage note====
The plant and the writing material made from it are usually regarded as uncountable, as with [[grass]] and [[paper]]. The plural [[papyri]] is more prevelent when referring to surviving ancient manuscripts written on papyrus.

